The paper deals with graphical models for linear codes, which are primarily studied in the information theory (cs.IT) community. The paper also discusses the complexity of these models, which is a topic of interest in the computer science (cs.DS) community. The use of graphical models is also relevant to the fields of statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses heuristics for extracting novel graphical models, which could be of interest to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) community.
